column2: Lipid Mediators of inflammation in BALF 3-19 days after infection with Influenza

In this study broncho-alveolar lavage fluid (BALF) from mice infected with influenza A virus, PR8 (200 PFU and 2x10^5 PFU), X31 (2x10^5 PFU) was analyzed for lipidomic host response in comparison with the mock infected animals. Time Points: 3, 5, 7, 9, 11, 13, 19 days post infection, done in 8-10 replicates.)
